# ─── API Environment ───

# Database connection string
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://hu_admin:localdev@localhost:5432/hu_partners?schema=public

# Server port
PORT=3001

# JWT secret (minimum 32 characters)
JWT_SECRET=change-me-to-a-secure-random-string-min-32-chars

# CORS allowed origin
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000

# Environment
NODE_ENV=development

#  Redis Variables: The application uses BullMQ for queues and requires Redis.                                                                   

REDIS_HOST : Host address of the Redis instance (defaults to  localhost ).                                                               
REDIS_PORT : Port of the Redis instance (defaults to  6379 ).                                                                            
(Note: The  docker-compose.yml  is passing  REDIS_URL , but the NestJS  BullModule  configuration in app.module.ts is currently configured to look for  REDIS_HOST  and  REDIS_PORT  instead).                                                                              

NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL : (Important) Although this is typically a frontend variable, the API utilizes it to generate absolute frontend links (e.g., for newsletter verification and unsubscribe emails in subscriptions.service.ts and newsletter.processor.ts).  